#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn54:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 54 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 54 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn54:0.2"
msgid "Potaliyasutta "
msgstr "With Potaliya the Wanderer "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn54:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn54:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅguttarāpesu viharati āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅguttarāpānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Northern Āpaṇas, near the town of theirs named Āpaṇa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn54:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āpaṇaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Āpaṇa for alms. "

msgctxt "mn54:2.2"
msgid "Āpaṇe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yenaññataro vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya. "
msgstr "He wandered for alms in Āpaṇa. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation. "

#. VAR: ajjhogāhetvā → ajjhogahetvā (bj, s1-3, km) | ajjhogāhitvā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
#. VAR: chattupāhanāhi → chattupāhano (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:3.1"
msgid "Potaliyopi kho gahapati sampannanivāsanapāvuraṇo chattupāhanāhi jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena so vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Potaliya the householder also approached that forest grove while going for a walk. He was well dressed in a cloak and sarong, with parasol and sandals. Having plunged deep into it, he went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn54:3.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "mn54:3.3"
msgid "“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”ti kupito anattamano tuṇhī ahosi. "
msgstr "When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he stayed silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.360, sc2
msgctxt "mn54:3.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "mn54:3.6"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and a third time the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "mn54:3.7"
msgid "“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”ti kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn54:3.9"
msgid "“tayidaṃ, bho gotama, nacchannaṃ, tayidaṃ nappatirūpaṃ, yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ gahapativādena samudācarasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, it is neither proper nor appropriate for you to address me as ‘householder’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.10"
msgid "“Te hi te, gahapati, ākārā, te liṅgā, te nimittā yathā taṃ gahapatissā”ti. "
msgstr "“Well, householder, you have the features, attributes, and signs of a householder.” "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-nuances-of-vohara/4136
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.11"
msgid "“Tathā hi pana me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, it’s because I have refused all work and cut off all judgments.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.12"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, gahapati, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti? "
msgstr "“Householder, in what way have you refused all work and cut off all judgments?” "

# NOTE: me … yam ahosi + “what I used to have”
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.13"
msgid "“Idha me, bho gotama, yaṃ ahosi dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā sabbaṃ taṃ puttānaṃ dāyajjaṃ niyyātaṃ, tatthāhaṃ anovādī anupavādī ghāsacchādanaparamo viharāmi. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, all the money, grain, gold, and silver I used to have has been handed over to my children as their inheritance. And in this matter I do not advise or reprimand them, but live with nothing more than food and clothes. "

#. VAR: Evaṃ kho me → evañca me (s1-3) | evaṃ me (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:3.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I have refused all work and cut off all judgments.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.15"
msgid "“Aññathā kho tvaṃ, gahapati, vohārasamucchedaṃ vadasi, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti. "
msgstr "“The cutting off of judgments as you describe it is one thing, householder, but the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training is quite different.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.16"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hoti? "
msgstr "“But what, sir, is cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training? "

msgctxt "mn54:3.17"
msgid "Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, please teach me this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.18"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:3.19"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc3
msgctxt "mn54:4.1"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: me → yeme pana (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn54:4.2"
msgid "“aṭṭha kho ime, gahapati, dhammā ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "“Householder, these eight things lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.3"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha? "
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "mn54:4.4"
msgid "Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo; "
msgstr "Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.5"
msgid "dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabbaṃ; "
msgstr "Stealing should be given up, relying on not stealing. "

#. VAR: saccavācaṃ → saccaṃ vācaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:4.6"
msgid "saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo; "
msgstr "Lying should be given up, relying on speaking the truth. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.7"
msgid "apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā; "
msgstr "Divisive speech should be given up, relying on speech that isn’t divisive. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.8"
msgid "agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo; "
msgstr "Greed and lust should be given up, relying on not being greedy and lustful. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.9"
msgid "anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo; "
msgstr "Blaming and insulting should be given up, relying on not blaming and not insulting. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.10"
msgid "akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo; "
msgstr "Anger and distress should be given up, relying on not being angry and distressed. "

msgctxt "mn54:4.11"
msgid "anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo. "
msgstr "Arrogance should be given up, relying on not being arrogant. "

#. VAR: vitthārena → vitthāretvā (mr)
msgctxt "mn54:4.12"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapati, aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena avibhattā, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the eight things—stated in brief without being analyzed in detail—that lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn54:5.1"
msgid "“Ye me, bhante, bhagavatā aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena avibhattā, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti, sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā ime aṭṭha dhamme vitthārena vibhajatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, please teach me these eight things in detail out of compassion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:5.2"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn54:5.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya. "

msgctxt "mn54:5.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli1.361, sc4
msgctxt "mn54:6.1"
msgid "“‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "“‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures.’ That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn54:6.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple reflects: "

msgctxt "mn54:6.3"
msgid "‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu pāṇātipātī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno. "
msgstr "‘I am practicing to give up and cut off the fetters that might cause me to kill living creatures. "

#. VAR: Ahañceva → ahañce (?)
#. VAR: anuviccāpi maṃ viññū → anuvicca viññū (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn54:6.4"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana pāṇātipātī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya pāṇātipātapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ pāṇātipātapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā pāṇātipātapaccayā. "
msgstr "But if I were to kill living creatures, because of that I would reprimand myself; sensible people, after examination, would criticize me; and when my body breaks up, after death, I could expect to be reborn in a bad place. "

msgctxt "mn54:6.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ pāṇātipāto. "
msgstr "And killing living creatures is itself a fetter and a hindrance. "

msgctxt "mn54:6.6"
msgid "Ye ca pāṇātipātapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, pāṇātipātā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’. "
msgstr "The distressing and feverish defilements that might arise because of killing living creatures do not occur in someone who does not kill living creatures.’ "

msgctxt "mn54:6.7"
msgid "‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti—"
msgstr "‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures.’ "

msgctxt "mn54:6.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc5
msgctxt "mn54:7.1"
msgid "‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Stealing … "

msgctxt "mn54:7.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.3"
msgid "‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu adinnādāyī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.4"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana adinnādāyī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya adinnādānapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ adinnādānapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā adinnādānapaccayā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.5"
msgid "Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ adinnādānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.6"
msgid "Ye ca adinnādānapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā adinnādānā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.7"
msgid "‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:7.8"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.362, sc6
msgctxt "mn54:8.1"
msgid "‘Saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "lying … "

msgctxt "mn54:8.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:8.3"
msgid "‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu musāvādī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn54:8.4"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana musāvādī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya musāvādapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ musāvādapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā musāvādapaccayā. "
msgstr " "

